entry.title: WEATHER ADVISORY , Killarney
entry.summary: Persons in or near this area should be on the lookout for adverse weather conditions and take necessary safety precautions. Issued: 05:24 AM EST Saturday 25 February 2023

entry.title: Saturday: Flurries. High minus 6.
entry.summary: Flurries ending this afternoon then cloudy with 60 percent chance of flurries. Risk of snow squalls this morning and early this afternoon. Local amount 5 cm. Wind becoming east 20 km/h gusting to 40 this morning then light early this afternoon. High minus 6. Wind chill minus 24 this morning and minus 10 this afternoon. UV index 1 or low. Forecast issued 05:30 AM EST Saturday 25 February 2023

entry.title: Saturday night: Flurries. Low minus 9.
entry.summary: Cloudy. 60 percent chance of flurries this evening. Flurries beginning late this evening. Amount 2 to 4 cm. Wind becoming southwest 20 km/h gusting to 40 late this evening. Low minus 9. Wind chill minus 8 this evening and minus 16 overnight. Forecast issued 05:30 AM EST Saturday 25 February 2023

entry.title: Sunday: Chance of flurries. High minus 2. POP 40%
